# rarpar License

rarpar source code is licensed under GPL-3.0-or-later.

Normal rarpar binary distributions include and link `weaver-unrar`. Those
binary distributions therefore carry the additional UnRAR source-code
restriction for the RAR extraction and recovery code.

Binary release archives include:

- `LICENSE`: this rarpar license notice.
- `LICENSE.GPL-3.0-or-later`: the full GNU GPL version 3 text.
- `LICENSE.weaver-unrar`: the complete weaver-unrar license text, including
  the UnRAR source-code restriction.

Source checkouts include the full GNU GPL version 3 text in the workspace root
`LICENSE` file and the complete weaver-unrar license in
`crates/weaver-unrar/LICENSE`.

## UnRAR Source-Code Restriction

UnRAR source code may be used in any software to handle
RAR archives without limitations free of charge, but cannot be
used to develop RAR (WinRAR) compatible archiver and to
re-create RAR compression algorithm, which is proprietary.
Distribution of modified UnRAR source code in separate form
or as a part of other software is permitted, provided that
full text of this paragraph, starting from "UnRAR source code"
words, is included in license, or in documentation if license
is not available, and in source code comments of resulting package.
